# Library vs playground

- **`field-demo/projects/field-ui/`** — Publishable **library** using Angular signals (`input()`, `computed()`, `viewChild()`). Exports: `FieldStandardComponent`, `FieldIconComponent`, `FieldIconRegistry`, `SuggestPanelComponent`, `FigmaIconService`, plus types. Design tokens split into `_colors.scss`, `_typography.scss`, `_dimensions.scss`, `_dropdown.scss` (barrel: `_tokens.scss`). **No** playground-only code.
- **`field-demo/projects/playground/`** — **Demo app**: `ThemeService` (signal-based), `SuggestOptionsService` (localStorage persistence), reusable sub-components (`ToggleSwitchComponent`, `IconPickerComponent`, `SuggestEditorComponent`). Playground-specific CSS custom properties (`--pg-*`) defined in `styles.scss`. Consumes **`field-ui`** via **`public-api.ts`**; **library must not depend on the playground.**

Put shared design-system API in **`field-ui`**; everything else in **`playground`** or a future sibling under **`Field/`**.
